WEBVTT

00:01.920 --> 00:03.850
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:09.630 --> 00:15.470
ANNOUNCER: And now DreamWorks'
"The Penguins of Madagascar."

00:15.470 --> 00:18.930
[THEME MUSIC]

00:35.560 --> 00:36.260
-Hit it!

00:36.260 --> 00:39.460
[THEME MUSIC]

00:51.290 --> 00:52.150
-Cute and cuddly, boys.

00:56.770 --> 00:58.730
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:07.080 --> 01:08.550
[ALARM RINGING]

01:11.930 --> 01:15.130
-Skipper, we're picking up
an outgoing airborne target.

01:15.130 --> 01:16.860
-It's on a north by
southwest heading.

01:16.860 --> 01:18.990
Air speed-- two
and a half knots.

01:18.990 --> 01:21.340
-Altitude is four metres
and climbing fast.

01:21.340 --> 01:23.490
Five metres, six metres--

01:23.490 --> 01:26.380
-Private, you know I feel
about the metric system.

01:26.380 --> 01:28.230
We go with feet and inches.

01:28.230 --> 01:29.790
-Identifying target now.

01:29.790 --> 01:32.340
It looks like we have
another runaway red

01:32.340 --> 01:33.430
on our hands, Skipper.

01:33.430 --> 01:35.870
-Why is it always the red ones?

01:35.870 --> 01:37.350
-My balloon!

01:37.350 --> 01:38.830
[CRYING]

01:45.960 --> 01:47.720
-On my mark-- now!

01:57.600 --> 01:59.090
-Huh?

01:59.090 --> 02:01.310
BOTH: Yeah!

02:01.310 --> 02:04.930
-Gentlemen, today's
operation was a success.

02:04.930 --> 02:06.170
[CHEERING]

02:06.170 --> 02:11.570
-However, I have to ask, are
we ready for the big one?

02:11.570 --> 02:13.130
-The big one?

02:13.130 --> 02:15.040
-El grande enchilada.

02:15.040 --> 02:16.700
-Yum.

02:16.700 --> 02:19.380
-Not the eating kind of
enchilada-- the "in your face,

02:19.380 --> 02:22.630
knock you on your posterior"
kind of enchilada.

02:22.630 --> 02:26.010
-So it's not actually food?

02:26.010 --> 02:29.900
-Kowalski, we don't know
what it actually is.

02:29.900 --> 02:32.170
-Then how can we know
if we're ready for it?

02:32.170 --> 02:33.940
-Well, that's what
today's all about.

02:33.940 --> 02:35.220
-The big one's today?

02:35.220 --> 02:36.320
-Affirmative.

02:36.320 --> 02:40.740
The big one is coming
today around 4:00-ish.

02:43.740 --> 02:48.190
Fortunately, I have spent months
preparing for the big one.

02:48.190 --> 02:51.940
And when my plan was complete,
I knew what I had to do.

02:51.940 --> 02:54.600
The plan was secured
in a lockbox.

02:54.600 --> 02:59.540
And under the cover of darkness,
I chose a top secret location,

02:59.540 --> 03:07.070
at which I buried the top secret
plan-- a remote area of the zoo

03:07.070 --> 03:09.910
where no human or
animal ever goes.

03:09.910 --> 03:11.860
-Until, of course, they
complete construction

03:11.860 --> 03:12.990
of the new children's zoo.

03:12.990 --> 03:13.690
SKIPPER: What?

03:13.690 --> 03:15.580
-That's where the children's
zoo is going to be.

03:15.580 --> 03:16.620
Groundbreaking is today.

03:16.620 --> 03:17.320
-Blast!

03:21.780 --> 03:23.750
-We only have four
hours until the big one.

03:23.750 --> 03:25.170
-We need those plans.

03:25.170 --> 03:26.190
-Perhaps a diversion.

03:26.190 --> 03:29.580
-Oh, it's "Live at Five"
Chuck Charles from the telly.

03:29.580 --> 03:32.450
-We're here live at
the Central Park Zoo

03:32.450 --> 03:36.250
for the groundbreaking of
the new children's zoo.

03:36.250 --> 03:39.180
-There's our diversion.

03:39.180 --> 03:40.240
I'm going in.

03:43.170 --> 03:44.750
-You think Skipper
needs back up?

03:44.750 --> 03:45.450
-Our Skipper?

03:45.450 --> 03:46.150
-Pfft.

03:49.690 --> 03:50.880
[CRASHING]

03:51.510 --> 03:52.210
-Skipper?

03:52.210 --> 03:53.370
-Awaiting orders.

03:53.370 --> 03:54.070
-Oh, boy.

03:54.070 --> 03:55.540
-We must get him out of there.

03:55.540 --> 03:56.700
What should we do?

03:56.700 --> 04:00.830
-Commence Operation Get
Skipper Out of the Locked Van.

04:00.830 --> 04:01.610
-The name needs work.

04:01.610 --> 04:02.490
But let's do it!

04:05.160 --> 04:05.860
-Ooh!

04:08.740 --> 04:10.190
-What was that?

04:10.190 --> 04:11.690
You were supposed to catch me.

04:11.690 --> 04:13.830
-No, we were supposed
to pick the lock.

04:13.830 --> 04:16.300
[MUMBLING]

04:16.300 --> 04:17.770
[CRASHING]

04:20.280 --> 04:21.590
[GROANING]

04:22.470 --> 04:23.790
-Skipper!

04:23.790 --> 04:26.750
-OK, who hid my hairspray?

04:26.750 --> 04:27.450
Hey!

04:27.450 --> 04:30.490
What happened in here?

04:30.490 --> 04:31.610
[GROANING]

04:32.310 --> 04:33.500
-Are you all right, Skipper?

04:33.500 --> 04:35.200
-Hey, get out of my shot.

04:35.200 --> 04:39.350
This is Chuck Charles with
your late-breaking local news.

04:39.350 --> 04:42.400
-Is-- is he talking to the wall?

04:42.400 --> 04:45.620
-Something horrible happened
inside that news van.

04:45.620 --> 04:47.770
-I wonder.

04:47.770 --> 04:50.150
Theoretically, it's possible
that the electrical receptors

04:50.150 --> 04:52.720
inside Skipper's brain picked
up the signals from that van

04:52.720 --> 04:55.040
and reprogrammed his functional
sensors to mimic the patterns

04:55.040 --> 04:56.650
of behaviour shown
on the broadcasts.

04:56.650 --> 04:57.570
-You mean--

04:57.570 --> 05:00.000
-Yes, I think we can
safely say that Skipper

05:00.000 --> 05:03.150
is stricken with anchor-manesia.

05:03.150 --> 05:04.240
-I'm Chuck Charles.

05:04.240 --> 05:06.370
And we're your "Live
at Five" news team--

05:06.370 --> 05:09.620
Gil Force with weather,
Scooter Alvarez on sports,

05:09.620 --> 05:13.060
and as always, my
co-anchor, Bonnie Chang.

05:13.060 --> 05:14.640
-Bonnie Chang?

05:14.640 --> 05:16.970
-But the big one is coming.

05:16.970 --> 05:18.350
We still need those plans.

05:18.350 --> 05:19.950
And even if we get
the plans, we still

05:19.950 --> 05:21.080
need Skipper to be Skipper.

05:23.980 --> 05:26.580
-All right, I will
randomly combine liquids

05:26.580 --> 05:30.740
and powders until I find a cure.

05:30.740 --> 05:33.170
This could take a while.

05:33.170 --> 05:36.420
-I'm with the "Live at Five"
news team here on the scene.

05:36.420 --> 05:38.770
-You are a penguin.

05:38.770 --> 05:40.650
-How's that weekend
forecast, Gil?

05:40.650 --> 05:41.560
-I'm Private.

05:41.560 --> 05:42.660
Look, I waddle.

05:42.660 --> 05:44.290
And you waddle too
because you're a--

05:44.290 --> 05:45.150
-Chuck Charles.

05:45.150 --> 05:46.480
And I know the news.

05:49.720 --> 05:52.140
-Look!

05:52.140 --> 05:54.010
Penguins swim.

05:54.010 --> 05:55.920
-Well, Gil, looks
like another wet--

06:00.050 --> 06:03.440
--[COUGHING], and
that's the news.

06:03.440 --> 06:04.290
[SIGHING]

06:04.290 --> 06:05.550
-Status report?

06:05.550 --> 06:06.660
-Still Chuck Charles.

06:06.660 --> 06:09.690
-And the anchor-manesia cure
is a bit behind schedule.

06:09.690 --> 06:10.890
[BELL CHIMING]

06:10.890 --> 06:13.470
-We-- we only have one hour.

06:13.470 --> 06:16.890
-Yeah, I need at
least 7,000 years.

06:16.890 --> 06:19.380
[MUMBLING]

06:20.380 --> 06:23.580
-Don't worry, Rico,
Skipper's-- gone?

06:23.580 --> 06:26.340
-Here's your "Live at Five"
exclusive interview with--

06:26.340 --> 06:28.750
-King Julien, yes.

06:28.750 --> 06:30.570
But you can call me King Julien.

06:30.570 --> 06:33.350
-Do you have any comment
about the rumours?

06:33.350 --> 06:34.900
-Eh, what rumours?

06:34.900 --> 06:36.120
-Oh, don't play coy.

06:36.120 --> 06:40.380
We all know what they're
saying about your royal family.

06:40.380 --> 06:41.080
-Lies!

06:41.080 --> 06:42.310
All lies!

06:42.310 --> 06:43.510
This interview over.

06:43.510 --> 06:47.140
-And we're out.

06:47.140 --> 06:48.600
Fantastic interview.

06:48.600 --> 06:50.980
-Well, thank you.

06:50.980 --> 06:52.030
Care for some fruit?

06:52.030 --> 06:54.800
It is tasty and nice,
except maybe the grapes.

06:54.800 --> 06:56.180
I'm not 100% on those.

06:56.180 --> 06:58.400
-Could your grapes
be poisoning you?

06:58.400 --> 06:59.460
Find out at 5:00.

06:59.460 --> 07:03.090
And we're out.

07:03.090 --> 07:03.790
-Ooh!

07:03.790 --> 07:04.940
News I can use.

07:04.940 --> 07:06.180
-Let's not be running off.

07:06.180 --> 07:07.250
SKIPPER: Chuck Charles has the--

07:10.900 --> 07:14.680
-The technical term for
our situation is done-sky.

07:14.680 --> 07:17.580
-Bonnie, are you doing something
different with your hair?

07:17.580 --> 07:19.270
I like it.

07:19.270 --> 07:21.790
-Skipper would want us
to go get those plans.

07:21.790 --> 07:23.610
-But how can we do
that when Skipper--

07:23.610 --> 07:26.280
-Now over to Scooter
Alvarez with the highlights

07:26.280 --> 07:27.680
and the lowlights.

07:27.680 --> 07:29.870
-I am not Scooter Alvarez!

07:29.870 --> 07:32.080
I don't even know what
a Scooter Alvarez is!

07:32.080 --> 07:34.710
-OK, we're just gonna have
to-- to do it without him.

07:34.710 --> 07:35.410
-But--

07:35.410 --> 07:36.110
-I know.

07:36.110 --> 07:37.670
But what choice do we have?

07:37.670 --> 07:39.530
Skipper would want us
to carry on without him.

07:39.530 --> 07:40.760
-Keep an eye on Scooter.

07:40.760 --> 07:42.470
He's not quite himself today.

07:42.470 --> 07:46.900
-Uh, no, I'm here with
those scores or my name's

07:46.900 --> 07:49.040
not Scooter Alvarado.

07:49.040 --> 07:49.770
-Alvarez.

07:49.770 --> 07:50.530
-Exactly.

07:50.530 --> 07:51.300
-OK.

07:51.300 --> 07:53.780
Uh, we're gonna go out
for a while, Chuck.

07:53.780 --> 07:58.300
Um, so you just stay
here in the studio.

07:58.300 --> 08:02.740
-According to the map, we
should be digging over there.

08:02.740 --> 08:05.350
-With all this construction,
there are too many witnesses.

08:05.350 --> 08:07.370
-Must think.

08:07.370 --> 08:08.730
-What would Skipper do?

08:08.730 --> 08:12.140
-Precariously perch himself
high atop the crane?

08:12.140 --> 08:13.550
-I don't see how
that would help.

08:13.550 --> 08:17.390
-Oh, it won't, but that
is what Skipper's doing.

08:17.390 --> 08:19.870
-This is your "Live at
Five" eye in the sky.

08:19.870 --> 08:20.570
[SIGHING]

08:20.570 --> 08:22.930
-He is not making this easy.

08:22.930 --> 08:23.900
-Easy?

08:23.900 --> 08:26.110
Was it easy for
Manfredi and Johnson

08:26.110 --> 08:27.880
when that undersea
escape tunnel turned out

08:27.880 --> 08:29.900
to be the business
end of a beluga whale?

08:29.900 --> 08:31.540
They couldn't even
speak for a month.

08:31.540 --> 08:33.270
-And even then,
it was gibberish.

08:33.270 --> 08:36.210
-So if this is gonna be
hard, that's fine with me.

08:36.210 --> 08:37.160
-Yeah.

08:37.160 --> 08:41.630
-Let's do this thing-- and all
other things required of us.

08:48.890 --> 08:50.830
-Hi-ya!

08:50.830 --> 08:52.360
-Can you describe
to the folks at home

08:52.360 --> 08:54.760
how you're feeling right now?

08:54.760 --> 08:55.760
[GROANING]

08:57.450 --> 08:59.690
-You heard it here first.

08:59.690 --> 09:01.380
This is Chuck Charles reporting.

09:06.480 --> 09:09.450
-Do I connect the red one to
the blue one or the blue one

09:09.450 --> 09:11.020
to the red one?

09:11.020 --> 09:11.870
-I dunno.

09:11.870 --> 09:15.810
-That's the sort of thing
Skipper would normally decide.

09:15.810 --> 09:16.660
-Now be honest with me.

09:16.660 --> 09:20.140
Do you like my good side
or my even better side?

09:20.140 --> 09:23.050
-But there isn't anything
normal about this.

09:23.050 --> 09:24.770
-Perhaps if I bypass-- whoa!

09:28.540 --> 09:29.240
-Stop!

09:40.180 --> 09:41.700
I see the plans!

09:41.700 --> 09:42.590
Come on!

09:42.590 --> 09:43.290
We have to hurry!

09:43.290 --> 09:45.060
[COUGHING]

09:46.540 --> 09:47.530
-Got it!

09:47.530 --> 09:48.230
-Yes!

09:48.230 --> 09:49.060
-Yes!

09:49.060 --> 09:50.500
Yes!

09:50.500 --> 09:51.200
What did we do?

09:51.200 --> 09:53.540
-How should I know
who moved the dozer?

09:57.440 --> 10:00.000
-Our top story, Chuck
Charles and the news team

10:00.000 --> 10:00.700
get buried alive.

10:05.240 --> 10:08.340
-Well, at least we saved
the top secret plans.

10:08.340 --> 10:10.000
-Although it might have
been preferable to not

10:10.000 --> 10:11.530
be buried alive with them.

10:11.530 --> 10:12.710
[MUMBLING]

10:13.900 --> 10:16.350
-Yes, Rico, it is
just about 4:00-ish.

10:16.350 --> 10:18.590
-Then we'd better check out
Skipper's top secret plan.

10:18.590 --> 10:20.430
[COUGHING]

10:23.640 --> 10:26.310
-What?

10:26.310 --> 10:29.280
SKIPPER (VOICEOVER): Is the
team ready for the big one?

10:29.280 --> 10:30.540
We shall see.

10:30.540 --> 10:31.370
-Afraid not.

10:31.370 --> 10:32.380
-But what is it?

10:32.380 --> 10:33.480
Some sort of natural disaster?

10:33.480 --> 10:34.680
SKIPPER (VOICEOVER):
You might think

10:34.680 --> 10:38.660
it might be some sort of natural
disaster, but you'd be wrong.

10:38.660 --> 10:42.660
No, the big one is the
greatest challenge of all.

10:42.660 --> 10:45.340
What happens if one
member of the team is out?

10:45.340 --> 10:49.070
What if we didn't have young
Private's heart, Kowalski's

10:49.070 --> 10:52.280
brains, or Rico's appetite
for reckless destruction?

10:52.280 --> 10:53.680
-I dunno.

10:53.680 --> 10:54.620
-Oh.

10:54.620 --> 10:56.110
I suppose that would be bad.

10:56.110 --> 10:58.900
-Or what if the team
leader were inexplicably

10:58.900 --> 11:01.780
acting like a pompous anchorman?

11:01.780 --> 11:04.850
-What if-- indeed?

11:04.850 --> 11:07.870
-Yes, what if-- ooh!

11:07.870 --> 11:09.430
-Hang on.

11:09.430 --> 11:10.570
You were faking it!

11:10.570 --> 11:11.480
-Bingo.

11:11.480 --> 11:13.130
-It was all a test?

11:13.130 --> 11:14.950
-And the team came through.

11:14.950 --> 11:15.800
Huzzah!

11:15.800 --> 11:17.300
-We're ready for the big one!

11:17.300 --> 11:18.470
-Yes, we are.

11:18.470 --> 11:20.030
We are also running
out of oxygen.

11:20.030 --> 11:21.520
-What?

11:21.520 --> 11:23.400
-Kowalski, give me options.

11:23.400 --> 11:25.380
-Rico sets an explosive
charge under this,

11:25.380 --> 11:27.580
blasting it straight up
through the dirt and rock.

11:27.580 --> 11:28.770
-And we all hang onto it.

11:28.770 --> 11:30.710
-Ooh, says like a wild ride.

11:30.710 --> 11:31.410
Rico.

11:31.410 --> 11:32.970
[COUGHING]

11:35.200 --> 11:36.600
[EXPLODING]

11:36.600 --> 11:39.510
-I don't get how a bulldozer
just turns on by itself.

11:49.090 --> 11:50.310
-Woo-hoo!

11:50.310 --> 11:51.240
-We did it!

11:51.240 --> 11:53.440
-We kicked big one's butt.

11:53.440 --> 11:55.140
-And we're out!

11:57.810 --> 11:59.780
[MUSIC PLAYING]

12:12.110 --> 12:14.660
-Maurice, this
smoothie is the yuck.

12:14.660 --> 12:15.870
Make me a better one.

12:15.870 --> 12:17.710
-You got it, your Majesty.

12:17.710 --> 12:19.160
I'll make you a better one.

12:28.160 --> 12:29.210
[SNICKERING]

12:29.210 --> 12:30.470
[SLURPING]

12:30.470 --> 12:32.320
-Mm.

12:32.320 --> 12:36.890
Now that is a smoothie
I can call groovy.

12:36.890 --> 12:39.300
-That's cause of the
secret ingredient.

12:39.300 --> 12:42.070
-It's the same
smoothie just grosser.

12:42.070 --> 12:43.380
-Got you, Maurice.

12:43.380 --> 12:45.400
-I just don't feel
right about this.

12:45.400 --> 12:46.100
-Shh!

12:52.560 --> 12:54.550
-(SINGING) Made a mistake
when you messed with me.

12:54.550 --> 12:56.530
Should've known
better and let it be!

12:56.530 --> 12:58.030
Making dumb choices
is one of your flaws!

12:58.030 --> 13:00.010
So look out, baby,
here come the claws!

13:00.010 --> 13:01.010
Yeah!

13:01.010 --> 13:03.490
Here comes the claws!

13:03.490 --> 13:04.490
Yeah-hoo!

13:04.490 --> 13:06.470
Here comes the claws!

13:10.000 --> 13:11.800
-Embarrassing, Marlene.

13:11.800 --> 13:13.070
Quite embarrassing.

13:13.070 --> 13:14.600
-I still don't feel right--

13:14.600 --> 13:16.410
-Shh, shh, shh.

13:16.410 --> 13:17.900
[SNORING]

13:23.350 --> 13:25.020
[MUMBLING]

13:27.300 --> 13:29.880
-OK, Mr. Bunny, time
to make night-night.

13:32.780 --> 13:34.360
[MUMBLING]

13:36.520 --> 13:39.340
-Bingy likes his bunny, eh?

13:39.340 --> 13:40.470
Interesting.

13:40.470 --> 13:41.420
-I just don't feel--

13:41.420 --> 13:42.830
-Shh, shh, shh, shh,
shh, shh, shh, shh.

13:42.830 --> 13:43.530
Shh!

13:45.990 --> 13:49.510
Gentlemen, Operation
Sneaky Peek is a success.

13:49.510 --> 13:52.560
-We now have sensitive intel
on every animal in the zoo.

13:52.560 --> 13:55.640
-But, Skipper, aren't
the animals are friends?

13:55.640 --> 13:58.480
-Young Private, a
friend is just an enemy

13:58.480 --> 13:59.850
who hasn't attacked yet.

13:59.850 --> 14:02.020
-That's not very
friendly thinking.

14:02.020 --> 14:02.930
-I know!

14:02.930 --> 14:04.470
Why are they attacking us?

14:04.470 --> 14:06.560
-This collection
of sordid secrets

14:06.560 --> 14:09.920
guarantees that we'll have the
upper flipper when they do.

14:09.920 --> 14:13.850
-Still, holding these secrets
is an awesome responsibility.

14:13.850 --> 14:17.150
If any were to leak,
it would be chaos.

14:17.150 --> 14:20.350
That's why I'm classifying
Operation Sneaky Peek

14:20.350 --> 14:23.710
tip-top tippy-top
top-top secret.

14:23.710 --> 14:24.540
-Oh!

14:24.540 --> 14:26.310
-Wow.

14:26.310 --> 14:29.080
-That's even more secret-y
than your delicious monkfish

14:29.080 --> 14:30.370
surprise recipe.

14:30.370 --> 14:31.350
-Exactly.

14:31.350 --> 14:34.360
So if anyone asks, you
didn't see anything.

14:34.360 --> 14:35.750
[KNOCKING]

14:35.750 --> 14:39.000
KOWALSKI: Uh, Skipper?

14:39.000 --> 14:42.810
-One and two and three
and four and-- Private,

14:42.810 --> 14:45.780
put a little hustle
in your muscle.

14:45.780 --> 14:46.940
-Sorry, Skipper.

14:46.940 --> 14:48.430
Didn't sleep well last night.

14:48.430 --> 14:52.480
I kept thinking
about Operation Sn--

14:52.480 --> 14:55.630
-Private, those words must
never be spoken aloud.

14:55.630 --> 14:56.330
-Sorry.

14:56.330 --> 14:57.490
-Tell you what.

14:57.490 --> 15:00.510
Skip the callisthenics and
go get yourself some chow.

15:00.510 --> 15:02.490
-Aye, aye, Skipper.

15:02.490 --> 15:04.800
-Tenderhearted tenderfoot.

15:04.800 --> 15:07.500
Kowalski, make a note to ring
that tenderness right out

15:07.500 --> 15:08.250
of him.

15:08.250 --> 15:09.230
-Aye, Skipper.

15:09.230 --> 15:10.580
[SIGHING]

15:12.380 --> 15:13.320
-Hm.

15:13.320 --> 15:15.590
Needs a little something.

15:15.590 --> 15:16.580
Hot sauce!

15:16.580 --> 15:17.280
Perfect!

15:17.280 --> 15:20.200
That ought to give these
sardines a little kick.

15:20.200 --> 15:23.590
-Mm, not bad.

15:23.590 --> 15:24.870
-Good workout, men.

15:24.870 --> 15:27.160
-Tesla's coil!

15:27.160 --> 15:28.000
[GROANING]

15:28.720 --> 15:30.060
-Please, tell me
you didn't consume

15:30.060 --> 15:31.560
the contents of this bottle.

15:31.560 --> 15:32.380
-I did.

15:32.380 --> 15:34.390
The hot sauce was very tasty.

15:34.390 --> 15:36.270
-This wasn't hot sauce.

15:36.270 --> 15:37.680
It was truth serum.

15:37.680 --> 15:40.240
-You put truth serum
in a hot sauce bottle?

15:40.240 --> 15:42.700
-Pfft, of course.

15:42.700 --> 15:43.940
-Hot sauce is truth serum.

15:43.940 --> 15:45.400
Grape jelly is sleeping gas.

15:45.400 --> 15:48.220
And ketchup is amnesia mist.

15:48.220 --> 15:49.840
Where was I?

15:49.840 --> 15:50.660
-And what's mustard?

15:50.660 --> 15:53.570
-Well, it's a tangy condiment
you put on your hot dog.

15:53.570 --> 15:56.110
-Mm, sounds delicious.

15:56.110 --> 15:57.600
-Point is, for the
next few hours,

15:57.600 --> 15:59.340
Private will be
unable to do anything

15:59.340 --> 16:01.010
but tell the truth,
the whole truth,

16:01.010 --> 16:02.670
and nothing but the truth.

16:02.670 --> 16:03.390
Observe.

16:03.390 --> 16:07.160
Private, do you honestly like
Skipper's monkfish surprise?

16:07.160 --> 16:09.200
-No, it tastes like
elephant sweat.

16:09.200 --> 16:14.670
But everyone pretends to like it
to spare Skipper's fragile ego.

16:14.670 --> 16:18.440
-My whole life is a lie!

16:18.440 --> 16:21.290
-So we've established
the effectiveness

16:21.290 --> 16:22.600
of the truth serum.

16:22.600 --> 16:25.100
-OK, OK, this
wont' be a problem.

16:25.100 --> 16:28.260
I mean, it's not like we
have anything to hide, right?

16:28.260 --> 16:29.650
[CLEARING THROAT]

16:30.570 --> 16:31.490
-Oh, yeah.

16:31.490 --> 16:32.940
ANIMAL: Help!

16:32.940 --> 16:34.970
-A desperate cry for help.

16:34.970 --> 16:35.670
Roll out, men.

16:38.660 --> 16:40.540
Private, mum's the word.

16:40.540 --> 16:42.020
-OK, Skipper.

16:42.020 --> 16:43.610
-I don't know how
he got in there,

16:43.610 --> 16:45.930
but if we don't get him out
soon, he'll be buried alive.

16:45.930 --> 16:47.720
-Help!

16:47.720 --> 16:48.420
Yum.

16:48.420 --> 16:52.410
I am, mm, trapped!

16:52.410 --> 16:53.750
-Ladder formation on three.

16:53.750 --> 16:55.390
Uno, dos, three!

16:59.640 --> 17:01.130
[LAUGHING]

17:01.130 --> 17:02.470
-I'm free!

17:02.470 --> 17:03.590
[CHEERING]

17:05.270 --> 17:06.720
-Yay!

17:06.720 --> 17:08.830
-Oh, thank you, penguins.

17:08.830 --> 17:13.020
I was really getting worried
about the pop-ity-corn!

17:13.020 --> 17:14.380
-Sure, happy to help.

17:14.380 --> 17:16.080
Now if you'll excuse us.

17:16.080 --> 17:17.070
-Why the rush?

17:17.070 --> 17:17.770
Stay.

17:17.770 --> 17:19.050
Celebrate.

17:19.050 --> 17:19.750
-No can do.

17:19.750 --> 17:21.680
Big fish to fry.

17:21.680 --> 17:22.380
-Come on.

17:22.380 --> 17:25.290
What are you actually afraid
you're gonna have some fun?

17:25.290 --> 17:27.280
-No, Marlene,
Skipper's afraid I'll

17:27.280 --> 17:29.540
tell everyone your
embarrassing secret.

17:29.540 --> 17:30.240
-Secret?

17:30.240 --> 17:31.570
What-- what secret?

17:31.570 --> 17:32.270
How did--

17:32.270 --> 17:35.250
-That you fancy yourself a
pop superstar and perform

17:35.250 --> 17:36.830
imaginary concerts every night.

17:36.830 --> 17:39.170
-How do you guys
know about that?

17:39.170 --> 17:40.820
Have you been spying on me?

17:40.820 --> 17:42.600
-Muffle the blabbermouth.

17:42.600 --> 17:46.740
-No, Marlene, we haven't
been spying on you.

17:46.740 --> 17:48.640
We've been spying on everyone.

17:48.640 --> 17:49.980
[GASPING]

17:50.780 --> 17:53.770
-We know all your secrets.

17:53.770 --> 17:56.310
Bing sucks his thumb.

17:56.310 --> 18:00.120
Phil cheats at chess.

18:00.120 --> 18:03.820
The spider monkeys
aren't even half spider.

18:03.820 --> 18:06.980
-Ooh, these are very
embarrassing secrets

18:06.980 --> 18:08.060
we are hearing.

18:08.060 --> 18:11.190
-Julien picks his nose.

18:11.190 --> 18:11.930
-Ahh!

18:11.930 --> 18:14.590
My secret gold
digging shame exposed!

18:14.590 --> 18:16.330
-Get him!

18:16.330 --> 18:18.290
-Mason is really Canadian.

18:18.290 --> 18:20.360
Burt has a--

18:20.360 --> 18:21.860
-Oh, no, you don't.

18:21.860 --> 18:25.020
I don't want anybody
knowing about that tattoo.

18:25.020 --> 18:27.510
I was young and foolish.

18:27.510 --> 18:29.180
And-- hey!

18:32.560 --> 18:35.940
-Look, tell anybody about
my Tijuana vacation,

18:35.940 --> 18:40.710
and I swear, buddy boy,
I'll stomp you into paste.

18:40.710 --> 18:42.410
-Kowalski, secure the Private!

18:42.410 --> 18:43.400
-Aye, Skipper.

18:47.310 --> 18:48.290
-Here he is.

18:48.290 --> 18:51.110
And there he goes.

18:51.110 --> 18:54.830
-Speak to me the most
juiciest of the gossips.

18:54.830 --> 18:58.070
-Mort loves you
just for your feet.

18:58.070 --> 19:00.290
-It's true!

19:00.290 --> 19:02.540
It's so true!

19:02.540 --> 19:03.960
-Well, duh.

19:03.960 --> 19:05.970
Come on, more with the spilling.

19:05.970 --> 19:06.760
And Maurice secretly--

19:06.760 --> 19:07.460
-OK.

19:07.460 --> 19:08.160
Thanks for coming.

19:08.160 --> 19:09.460
Bye.

19:09.460 --> 19:12.760
-What was he going
to say, Maurice?

19:12.760 --> 19:16.590
-That secretly I,
uh, think you're

19:16.590 --> 19:18.730
the greatest king
that ever lived.

19:18.730 --> 19:19.530
-Pfft!

19:19.530 --> 19:21.740
Maurice, that is no secret.

19:24.610 --> 19:25.780
-Rico, about face.

19:30.070 --> 19:30.770
-OK.

19:30.770 --> 19:32.990
So all I want to know is,
do you know about the--

19:32.990 --> 19:33.690
-Yes.

19:33.690 --> 19:34.390
-And how I like to--

19:34.390 --> 19:35.220
-Yes.
-With the--

19:35.220 --> 19:36.170
-Yes.

19:36.170 --> 19:37.170
-You know what?

19:37.170 --> 19:38.040
Not cool, guys.

19:38.040 --> 19:39.380
No, not cool at all.

19:39.380 --> 19:41.870
Friends don't spy on friends.

19:41.870 --> 19:43.090
I am so embarrassed.

19:43.090 --> 19:44.670
-If you think
that's embarrassing,

19:44.670 --> 19:46.800
you should see
what Kowalski does

19:46.800 --> 19:48.220
when he thinks no
one's watching.

19:51.140 --> 19:52.020
-Rico, floor it.

19:52.020 --> 19:53.360
[SCREECHING]

19:55.160 --> 19:56.170
Not in reverse.

19:56.170 --> 19:57.310
[SCREECHING]

19:58.590 --> 20:02.190
-Well, should be smooth
sailing from here.

20:02.190 --> 20:04.590
-Whoa!

20:04.590 --> 20:07.540
[ROARING]

20:07.540 --> 20:08.520
Bail out, men.

20:14.410 --> 20:16.170
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

20:16.870 --> 20:18.960
-Kowalski, status
on the angry mob.

20:18.960 --> 20:20.670
KOWALSKI: Mob still there.

20:20.670 --> 20:22.940
Mob still angry.

20:22.940 --> 20:24.270
-Oh.

20:24.270 --> 20:24.970
Hello.

20:24.970 --> 20:26.220
What's all this then?

20:26.220 --> 20:29.930
-Private, welcome
back from la-la land.

20:29.930 --> 20:31.210
-Um, thanks.

20:31.210 --> 20:32.240
Was I gone?

20:32.240 --> 20:33.200
SKIPPER: Yep.

20:33.200 --> 20:36.450
You accidentally spilled the
beans on Operation Sneaky Peek.

20:36.450 --> 20:38.840
-Oh, yes, I remember.

20:38.840 --> 20:39.930
Sorry, Skipper.

20:39.930 --> 20:41.650
-Not to worry, Private.

20:41.650 --> 20:43.790
We'll just stay safely
locked up in here

20:43.790 --> 20:44.790
until this whole thing is--

20:48.870 --> 20:50.780
-You penguins are gonna
pay for violating out

20:50.780 --> 20:54.100
inalienable rights of
privacy and whatnot.

20:54.100 --> 20:58.930
-Oh, what am I
supposed to do now?

20:58.930 --> 21:00.550
What's this?

21:00.550 --> 21:01.590
Amnesia spray-- fantastic.

21:04.120 --> 21:05.790
What's this?

21:05.790 --> 21:09.320
Amnesia spray, fantastic.

21:09.320 --> 21:11.290
What's this?

21:11.290 --> 21:14.320
Amnesia spray-- fantastic.

21:14.320 --> 21:17.300
-Hey, should I sit
on them individually?

21:17.300 --> 21:20.420
Or do I go for the group squish?

21:20.420 --> 21:21.320
-Why drag it out?

21:21.320 --> 21:23.330
I say one and done.

21:23.330 --> 21:25.750
-Kowalski, options?

21:25.750 --> 21:27.790
-Get fresh air while you can.

21:27.790 --> 21:28.840
[GASPING]

21:28.840 --> 21:30.560
-OK, here we go.

21:30.560 --> 21:32.390
I'm dropping booty.

21:32.390 --> 21:34.020
-No!

21:34.020 --> 21:34.820
-Hey, what's that?

21:34.820 --> 21:35.520
You hear something?

21:35.520 --> 21:36.630
PRIVATE: Forget!

21:36.630 --> 21:38.030
-I hear it too.

21:38.030 --> 21:40.500
-Forget, everybody!

21:40.500 --> 21:43.460
Forget!

21:43.460 --> 21:46.670
-What-- am I doing?

21:46.670 --> 21:49.080
-I'm feeling a little
discombobulated here.

21:49.080 --> 21:52.850
-Ooh, I'm kind--
kinda dizzy myself.

21:52.850 --> 21:55.100
I'm gonna sit down right here.

21:55.100 --> 21:56.410
[GROANING]

21:58.170 --> 22:00.760
-What have we done
to deserve this?

22:00.760 --> 22:03.340
-Watch where you park
that thing, pachyderm.

22:03.340 --> 22:07.370
-Sorry, didn't see you there.

22:07.370 --> 22:08.400
-What are we doing here?

22:08.400 --> 22:09.100
-I dunno.

22:09.100 --> 22:12.860
-I can't remember.

22:12.860 --> 22:14.210
-I remember.

22:14.210 --> 22:15.070
It is a party.

22:15.070 --> 22:17.570
A party for me.

22:17.570 --> 22:20.350
A me-esta, if you will.

22:20.350 --> 22:21.690
-A you-esta!

22:21.690 --> 22:22.580
Ole!

22:22.580 --> 22:25.200
-Now where are my gifts?

22:25.200 --> 22:27.510
Present me with the
presents already.

22:27.510 --> 22:28.960
[SIGHING]

22:30.830 --> 22:32.830
-You know, it's weird.

22:32.830 --> 22:36.600
I can't remember a thing
from the last week.

22:36.600 --> 22:40.480
-If it was worth remembering,
we'd remember it.

22:40.480 --> 22:43.210
-Rico, might I have
a stick of TNT?

22:43.210 --> 22:44.720
-Yup.

22:44.720 --> 22:45.420
KOWALSKI: Thanks.

22:48.940 --> 22:50.310
[EXPLODING]

22:51.020 --> 22:52.500
-Private, what was that?

22:52.500 --> 22:53.790
-Nothing, Skipper.

22:53.790 --> 22:55.340
Just my little secret.

22:55.340 --> 22:56.240
[GIGGLING]

22:59.240 --> 23:02.590
[THEME MUSIC]
